# The Listener — environment variables
#
# Everything here is OPTIONAL. The app works with no env vars at all using
# four zero-key sources (Google News, Bing News, Reddit, Bluesky).
#
# To use a variable: copy this file to `.env.local` (for `npm run dev`)
# or paste into Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.

# ── Storage ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Saved listeners persist to a JSON file by default. On Vercel, add the
# free "Upstash for Redis" integration from the Storage tab — it injects
# these automatically and the app switches to Redis with no code change.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
# Vercel KV equivalents are also supported:
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# ── Cron ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If set, /api/cron rejects requests without `Authorization: Bearer <value>`.
# Vercel Cron sends this header automatically once the env var exists.
# CRON_SECRET=

# ── Sign-in (Google OAuth via NextAuth) ───────────────────────────────
# The app now requires Google sign-in via Auth.js. Without these vars
# set, the sign-in page will fail. Steps:
#   1. console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Credentials →
#      Create OAuth 2.0 client ID → Web application.
#   2. Add redirect URI:  https://<your-domain>/api/auth/callback/google
#   3. Paste Client ID + Secret here.
#   4. Generate AUTH_SECRET with:  openssl rand -base64 32
#   5. Fill ALLOWED_EMAILS with the comma-separated list of emails
#      allowed to sign in (lowercase comparison).
# AUTH_SECRET=
# AUTH_GOOGLE_ID=
# AUTH_GOOGLE_SECRET=
# ALLOWED_EMAILS=you@gmail.com,teammate@gmail.com

# ── DEPRECATED: Password protection ────────────────────────────────────
# BASIC_AUTH was removed in favor of Google sign-in. These vars are
# now ignored. Safe to delete from Vercel.
# BASIC_AUTH_USER=
# BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD=

# ── Source keys (paid / optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
# X / Twitter via the official API. Paid at developer.x.com.
# TWITTER_BEARER=

# Apify token — unlocks X, Truth Social, Instagram, TikTok, Facebook
# and any actor on the Apify store. console.apify.com → Settings.
# APIFY_TOKEN=

# Brave News Search — broad news discovery. Free tier 2k queries/month.
# api.search.brave.com/app/keys
# BRAVE_API_KEY=

# Discord — bot must be a member of the server you want to read.
# discord.com/developers → New Application → Bot.
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# YouTube Data API — richer metadata for YouTube sources (the default
# per-channel RSS path works without this).
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY=

# ── Source bases (overrides — usually leave unset) ────────────────────
# Nitter instance used as the X fallback when no TWITTER_BEARER or
# APIFY_TOKEN is present. Public instances are often rate-limited.
# NITTER_BASE=https://nitter.net

# Truth Social Mastodon-style base. Default is the public site.
# TRUTH_SOCIAL_BASE=https://truthsocial.com

# Bluesky AppView. Default is the public, no-auth endpoint.
# BLUESKY_BASE=https://public.api.bsky.app

# Reddit requires a descriptive UA per their API rules.
# REDDIT_USER_AGENT=TheListener/1.0 (listening app)

# Optional CORS proxy prefix — only relevant if you self-host and need
# to route fetches through a proxy. The URL is appended URL-encoded.
# RLA_CORS_PROXY=https://your-proxy.example.com/?
